# Code style

## No comments

- Do not write comments. No JSDoc, no inline `//`, no block `/* */`, no banner separators.
- Names of variables and functions must carry the intent. If a comment is needed, rename instead.
- The single allowed exception is the frontmatter at the top of `.mdc` rule files.

## ASCII punctuation only

- Replace em-dashes (`—`) and en-dashes (`–`) with hyphens (`-`) in code, JSON, JSDoc, Markdown, HTML, locale strings.
- Replace curly quotes (`" " ' '`) with straight quotes (`" '`) in user-facing strings except when quoting a verbatim document excerpt.
- Replace `…` with `...`.

## Imports

- ES modules only (`import` / `export`). No CommonJS in `extension/`, `tests/`.
- One default export per file maximum; prefer named exports.

## Formatting and lint

- Prettier and ESLint are the source of truth. Run `npm run format` and `npm run lint` before committing.
- Do not silence lint rules with inline `eslint-disable` unless the rule itself is broken; fix the code instead.
